  "texts": [
    "The choice to employ logarithmically spaced amplitudes is driven by the exponential increase in the number of items in a uniformly distributed space as the distance from a central point increases.",
    "Logarithmic scaling tends to correct for this effect, resulting in a more linear distribution of distances of New Items from the centroid of the Studied Items.",
    "This value can be computed by applying the exponential function to the half of the ΔAIC between two models.",
    "In this case, specifically: exp(16 *.5)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}